To change the number type, it is necessary to visit a Customer Service Center with a valid ID. The service fee is 3 AZN.

A tariff primarily covers voice needs and may also include additional services such as internet and SMS. Tariffs can offer several services together or individually. A package is designed to meet a specific need (such as internet, calls, or SMS) and offers a fixed amount of service to the subscriber.

It’s possible to request this information by visiting a Bakcell Customer Service Center with a valid ID. Depending on the number of inquiries, the request will be answered within a maximum of 7 working days. The service fee is 5 AZN.

For ownership transfer, both the current and the new owner must visit a Bakcell Customer Service Center together with valid ID documents. The service fee is 4 AZN. For business and postpaid Klass numbers, the service is free of charge.

There are two types of power of attorney: General power of attorney and Special power of attorney. The general power of attorney allows all operations except number transfer to another person, issuance of a detailed invoice, and number sale. All other services can be performed without restrictions. The Special power of attorney allows number transfer to another person, issuance of a detailed invoice, sale of a number, and sale or activation of Asan İmza numbers. For transactions using a special power of attorney, the document must clearly state both the number and the specific operation to be performed.

"The number’s active period depends not on the current balance, but on the last top-up amount.
Top-up amount and validity period: 1.00 - 1.99 AZN — 4 days 2.00 - 2.99 AZN — 10 days 3.00 - 4.99 AZN — 20 days 5.00 - 9.99 AZN — 30 days 10.00 - 19.99 AZN — 50 days 20.00 - 49.99 AZN — 60 days 50.00 AZN and above — 120 days"
To check the registered owner of a number, dial *540#YES. The service fee is 0.10 AZN.

A detailed invoice can be obtained by visiting a Customer Service Center with an ID. The invoice covers usage over the last 6 months. The monthly service fee is 3 AZN. For business numbers, the service is free. It is also available free of charge via the Bakcell app.
To transfer a mobile number to Bakcell, visit a Customer Service Center or an official dealer with an ID. Full technical migration is completed within 3 business days.

Cancelling the current tariff requires switching to another one. A mobile number cannot be used without an active tariff, as the rates for calls, SMS, and internet depend on it. Bonuses within the current tariff will be removed during the switch. Switching between certain tariffs may be subject to a fee.
Terms of use set out the rules for users who want to access the mobile application. It is a legal document related to the protection of personal customer data.
A detailed invoice is available in the app under the “More” section.
It can be managed in the app via the “Manage number” and “Subscriptions” sections under “More”.

Along with a roaming package, the roaming service itself must also be active on the number. To activate the service, dial *121*1#YES. If already abroad, roaming can be activated by contacting customer care service.
Tap the card with your number and amount. You’ll be transferred to the page to see detailed information about your balance. Tap here on your balance or the “info” icon.
The summarized balance information can be viewed from the main page in the form of circle diagrams.

Go to the Package page by tapping the Package icon at the bottom of the main screen. Choose one of the bundles that fit you the best and activate it by tapping the “Activate” button or “+” icon on the list.

"Tap the circle diagrams of remaining usage on the main page, then tap the three dots icon of the package you want to deactivate. Tap “Deactivate” and confirm.
Go to dashboard, then tap account card, and then “Subscriptions”. Tap here the three dots icon of the package you want to deactivate. Tap “Deactivate” and confirm."

Bakcell provides a wide range of internet packages within the fastest mobile network. Feel free to choose any of the bundles for smartphone, tablet or computer, which fits you the best and enjoy the fastest mobile network.

"A duplicate of eSIM, Easy Signature, and 4G numbers can be obtained by visiting Bakcell's Customer Service Center or official dealers with an identity document. Additionally, a duplicate of the eSIM can be ordered through our official website and the Bakcell app. The service fee is 7 AZN, and there is no charge for business numbers."

Postpaid line – use now, pay later. This type of line allows flexible use of services with payment at the end of the month. The cost of calls, SMS, internet, and other services is calculated and provided as an invoice. Payments are made monthly, and a balance limit is applied. Prepaid line – pay first, then use. This line operates on a top-up basis, where the balance must be loaded in advance. Services can be used within the loaded amount. No invoice is issued for this tariff, and payment is made only for the services used.
